name: UrineDrugScreenForPainManagement
title: Urine drug screen for pain management
description: This value set was created for the express purpose of evaluating for evidence of substances that would be of concern to a provider who is considering opioid therapy for a patient.
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This value set contains terms that may be useful in evaluating urine drug screen results for adherence to prescribed therapy, diversion of prescribed medications, and/or misuse of illicit or prescribed medications in the context of chronic pain management.),(Data Element Scope: This value set contains terms defining urine drug screen tests that may be useful to monitor pharmacologic therapy during chronic pain management.),(Inclusion Criteria: Urine drug screen LOINC codes. Includes panel tests, quantitative and qualitative tests for opioids (and metabolites of opioid substances) and substances that would indicate abuse or illegal use of a substance, all of which a provider would want to be aware of before prescribing an opioid medication.),(Exclusion Criteria: Codes associated with therapeutic monitoring of medications without significant pharmacologic interactions with opiates or opioids. Codes associated with environmental toxins or contaminants.)
